quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  44,40,"On that Day no one shall be able to protect his friend, nor shall they receive any help"
  44,41,"except those to whom Allah will show His Mercy: for it is He Who is the All- Mighty, the All Merciful"
  44,42,Surely the Zaqqum tree
  44,43,shall be the food of the sinners
  44,44,it will be like the dregs of oil. Which shall boil in the belly
  44,45,like the boiling of scalding water
  44,46,"A voice will be heard: \"Seize him and drag him into the depth of the hell"
  44,47,then pour scalding water over his head
  44,48,"then the voice will say: \"Taste it; you were such a powerful noble"
  44,49,This is the punishment which you use to doubt
  44,50,"Indeed, this is what you used to dispute"
  44,51,"As for the righteous, they will be in a secure place"
  44,52,among gardens and springs
  44,53,"dressed in fine silk and rich brocade, sitting face to face"
  44,54,Such shall be their place! And We shall wed them to Hourin-Ayn (damsels with beautiful big and lustrous eyes)
  44,55,"There, in full peace, they shall call for every kind of fruit"
  44,56,"and after having prior death in the world, they shall taste death no more; and He (Allah) will protect them from the torment of hell"
  44,57,"as a grace from your Lord, and that will be the supreme achievement"
  44,58,Surely We have made this Qurâ€™an easy by revealing in your own language so that they may take heed
  44,59,If they do not accept the admonition then wait; surely they too are waiting